So, we don't sell it today.

43
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,719
Alright, then I'll have

44
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:29,719
oil-immersed marble goby,

45
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,039
spiced salt corn,

46
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:33,400
stir-fried beef ear with tendons,

47
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,960
and this one.

48
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:37,719
You've ordered so much.
Can you finish them all?

49
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:39,039
I'm only in Macau for a few days,

50
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:40,719
and leaving tomorrow, so I wanted

51
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,759
to order all the dishes I want to a try.

52
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:45,080
If you can't eat them all,
don't order that much.

53
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,719
If you can't eat them,

54
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:47,960
it means you are not destined to eat them.

55
00:03:48,639 --> 00:03:50,800
Come and eat next time.

56
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,000
Okay, then that's all.

57
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,319
Right, you are leaving tomorrow,

58
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:57,159
did you properly explore Macau?

59
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,479
I came here for work, on a business trip.

60
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:01,199
I just hanged around.

61
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:03,039
Young people

62
00:04:03,039 --> 00:04:04,360
are working so hard.

63
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,919
Just wait. I'll go place the order.

64
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,240
- Alright, thank you.
- Wei.

65
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,639
Brew a pot of tea for this lady.

66
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,224
Okay.

67
00:04:39,519 --> 00:04:41,000
Here it comes.

68
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,048
Thank you.

69
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,656
- How's it?
- Delicious.

70
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:13,120
Mango dessert, it's on me.

71
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:15,279
Thank you.

72
00:05:35,421 --> 00:05:37,959
<i>[Zhen Qiang]</i>

73
00:05:37,959 --> 00:05:38,959
Check please.

74
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:42,839
How was it? Was the food okay?

75
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,600
Very delicious. Everything is tasty.

76
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,720
Can I take away

77
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,800
another one of these?

78
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,959
This isn't from here.

79
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:50,160
I bought it from outside.

80
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,296
Then why…

81
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,752
You bought it from outside for me?

82
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,112
- Yes.
- Thank you.

83
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,800
Which shop did you buy it?

84
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,079
Maybe I'll look for it myself later.

85
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:07,199
I don't think you could find it.
They don't have a storefront.

86
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:10,480
It's an elderly couple,

87
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,160
pushing a food cart around.

88
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,600
But now they are getting old,

89
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,160
only go out to sell when they feel well.

90
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,319
So if you could eat it today,

91
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,319
you're lucky.

92
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:24,079
Alright, thank you.

93
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,680
Let me tell you, if next time you come,

94
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,920
I'm sure Zhen Qiang will still be here,

95
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:32,319
and you could definitely eat

96
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:34,759
spiced salt mantis shrimp.

97
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:38,959
Okay. If I have the chance
to come to Macau again,

98
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:41,199
I will definitely come
to eat the mantis shrimp.

99
00:06:41,199 --> 00:06:42,639
Okay.

100
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:44,120
388 yuan.

101
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,079
- E-payment, right?
- Okay.

102
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,136
Okay.

103
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,680
Okay, thank you.

104
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,864
Alright, it's paid. Thank you!

105
00:06:52,864 --> 00:06:54,720
Okay, see you.

106
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,879
Okay, then I'm off.

107
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,959
- Bye.
- Bye.

108
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,800
- What a coincidence!
- Such a coincidence.

109
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,519
You…

110
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,720
I've finished presenting the proposal today,

111
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,160
and went out for a meal.

112
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,319
- What about you?
- I just finished delivering takeout.

113
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,720
So, are you going to eat,

114
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,848
- or have you finished?
- Just finished.

115
00:07:51,879 --> 00:07:53,279
So,

116
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,439
are you heading back to the hotel now?

117
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,160
No, I wanted to take a walk.

118
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,199
I think you should let me take you around.

119
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,240
Are you done with your work?

120
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,480
I don't have much to do.

121
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:08,279
Besides, I should finish with what I started.

122
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,600
I'm your local guide,

123
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,480
so I should properly finish my job.

124
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,279
Alright, then where shall we go?

125
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,959
Let me think.

126
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,720
Let's head that way.

127
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,560
Alright.

128
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:27,439
Is the restaurant good?

129
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,312
Very good.

130
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,959
I think Macau

131
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:33,679
is a wonderful place.

132
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,159
Yes, because it's hard to find

133
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,559
a city

134
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:40,720
with so many

135
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,679
traditional Chinese cultural elements,

136
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:45,480
and many Western-style buildings.

137
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,720
Kind of fusion.

138
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,376
What I'm talking about is not
just architecture, but also the people.

139
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:54,320
- How?
- Just like that restaurant I had dinner,

140
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:56,080
the owner

141
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,519
was really nice and adorable.

142
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:59,080
I was sitting there,

143
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,440
and he chatted with me a lot.

144
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,600
In Macau, it feels like

145
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,399
between people, there is no…

146
00:09:07,519 --> 00:09:09,919
Guard.

147
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:11,360
Right.

148
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,440
No defenses, no pettiness.

149
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,120
And it's easy for people to get close.

150
00:09:16,759 --> 00:09:18,840
Do you remember what that restaurant is called?

151
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:21,000
Zhen Qiang.

152
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,639
- Have you eaten there?
- Zhen Qiang?

153
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,840
If you haven't, you'd definitely go try.

154
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,480
You must try it next time.

155
00:09:27,392 --> 00:09:29,080
Okay, I will give it a try.

156
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:35,744
Quite good.

157
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,519
Actually, I'm glad

158
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,480
that Macau brings you

159
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,720
so many good impressions.

160
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,559
I find it quite surprising too.

161
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:48,759
When I first came here,

162
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:50,120
I felt quite embarrassed.

163
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,840
I had no internet or money.

164
00:09:52,399 --> 00:09:54,080
And my work wasn't going smoothly either.

165
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,759
I felt like I was not even a modern person.

166
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,799
At that time,
I thought it's just a business trip,

167
00:09:58,799 --> 00:09:59,960
I could leave after a few days.

168
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:02,919
But now,

169
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:04,240
I don't want to leave.

170
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:08,000
That's great. Then stay a few more days.

171
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:10,360
Macau is small,

172
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,240
but I can take you

173
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,159
to lots of tasty and fun places.

174
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:18,440
But I really am here on business.

175
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:24,360
I know. I hope you can

176
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,799
come back to Macau sooner.

177
00:10:27,399 --> 00:10:28,480
I don't know.

178
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,639
I don't even know if my proposal will pass.

179
00:10:30,639 --> 00:10:32,000
What if it doesn't pass?

180
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,320
That's wonderful.

181
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,720
Take a long break and then come back to Macau.

182
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,879
Then I'll take you
to understand the real Macau.

183
00:10:54,688 --> 00:10:59,098
<i>[Josephineqer's Post]</i>

184
00:11:09,248 --> 00:11:13,568
<i>♫ I need your love ♫</i>

185
00:11:13,568 --> 00:11:17,472
<i>♫ To live my life ♫</i>

186
00:11:17,472 --> 00:11:23,261
<i>♫ I need someone like you ♫</i>

187
00:11:24,192 --> 00:11:27,616
<i>♫ I need your heart ♫</i>

188
00:11:28,352 --> 00:11:32,144
<i>♫ To beat with me ♫</i>

189
00:11:32,144 --> 00:11:38,016
<i>♫ Someone to see me through ♫</i>

190
00:11:39,112 --> 00:11:46,029
<i>♫ I need you by my side forever ♫</i>

191
00:11:47,171 --> 00:11:50,664
<i>♫ With you along ♫</i>

192
00:11:50,664 --> 00:11:54,560
<i>♫ I'm never lonely ♫</i>

193
00:11:55,488 --> 00:11:58,130
<i>♫ Someone to trust ♫</i>

194
00:11:58,130 --> 00:12:01,726
<i>♫ Someone like you ♫</i>

195
00:12:01,726 --> 00:12:08,437
<i>♫ I need your love be mine ♫</i>

196
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,184
Here.

197
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,639
Give you something wonderful

198
00:12:15,639 --> 00:12:17,240
of Macau.

199
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:19,360
- What is this?
- Herbal tea.

200
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,559
You don't usually drink herbal tea, do you?

201
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,720
- Yes.
- To cool down your internal heat.

202
00:12:27,879 --> 00:12:29,519
The herbal tea reminds me of something.

203
00:12:29,519 --> 00:12:30,960
I noticed that in Macau,

204
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,080
the tea cafes, the ice houses,

205
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,919
all close at six in the evening.

206
00:12:34,919 --> 00:12:36,320
Like the restaurant where I just had dinner

207
00:12:36,919 --> 00:12:38,279
doesn't open until five in the afternoon.

208
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:40,919
It feels like you all

209
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:44,200
don't want to make money.

210
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,248
That's not true.

211
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,080
We want to make money,

212
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,720
but we'll never make enough money.

213
00:12:50,799 --> 00:12:52,360
So if you don't enjoy your life

214
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:54,912
for making money,

215
00:12:55,519 --> 00:12:56,919
that'd be a loss.

216
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,080
Then listen to my everyday life.

217
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:06,480
I go to work and get off work every day,

218
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,000
and then continue to work overtime after work.

219
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,279
No matter how long I have slept,

220
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:11,072
I still have to make myself look good

221
00:13:11,072 --> 00:13:13,480
before going to work.

222
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,919
Going to work means catching the morning rush.

223
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:16,960
I can take a taxi,

224
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,480
but only by taking the metro

225
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,679
can I avoid traffic jams.

226
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:21,720
This way I can

227
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,879
punch in on time.

228
00:13:22,879 --> 00:13:24,840
If I am on consecutive business trips,

229
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,600
my suitcase will always stay in the living room

230
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,960
and there's no need to even close it,

231
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,519
just toss a few clothes into it

232
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:32,000
and then take it with you.

233
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,639
The house is more like

234
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,480
a hotel I stay at.

235
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:40,360
Work is my life.

236
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:44,399
Actually, I have also
experienced this kind of life.

237
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,320
But don't you think

238
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:50,000
you're very much like a non-player character?

239
00:13:50,559 --> 00:13:51,840
Doing a lot of work every day,

240
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:53,279
but none of them

241
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:55,000
are the tasks you should do.

242
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,279
But I still complete

243
00:13:58,279 --> 00:14:00,440
many complex and difficult tasks every day.

244
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,600
But they are all tasks
assigned to you by others.

245
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:06,000
And why make yourself

246
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,200
so tired and so tense?

247
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,159
I don't think ordinary people
have that much time

248
00:14:21,159 --> 00:14:23,120
to sit and ponder
whether they are tired or not.

249
00:14:24,639 --> 00:14:26,080
Because that's just what life is.

250
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,759
Year after year, day after day,
working hard without complaints.

251
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:31,879
Every day, everyone is fighting

252
00:14:31,879 --> 00:14:33,519
for the life that they've planned

253
00:14:33,519 --> 00:14:34,840
for themselves.

254
00:14:35,559 --> 00:14:37,399
Everyone lives like this.

255
00:14:37,399 --> 00:14:39,120
Yes, but I am not

256
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,440
talking about other people's lives.

257
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,639
I am talking about your life.

258
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,679
I think

259
00:15:07,679 --> 00:15:09,519
you are somewhat trapped in your work.

260
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,840
I think you are excellent,

261
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,039
and you don't need to prove it to anyone.

262
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,120
Just like that day we were
at the Calçada da Igreja de S. Lázaro,

263
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,840
I really wanted to invite you for a drink.

264
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:22,159
But you were too busy to sit down.

265
00:15:25,519 --> 00:15:27,120
You're here in Macau, why is that?

266
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:31,968
Yes.

267
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,320
But perhaps this is my life.

268
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,519
I just have to work hard for my life.

269
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,000
I'm not as lucky as you.

270
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,279
