00:30:32,319 --> 00:30:34,119
<i>Yesterday, I had a very pleasant time</i>

535
00:30:34,119 --> 00:30:35,359
<i>with Mr. Wei Shijie.</i>

536
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:55,799
I lost again.

537
00:30:56,319 --> 00:30:57,319
Why?

538
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,240
In that game, you had a queen
against a lone bishop.

539
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,559
You could have used the box method

540
00:31:01,559 --> 00:31:03,000
to complete the checkmate.

541
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,160
Create a constantly shrinking box

542
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,559
with your king and queen,

543
00:31:07,319 --> 00:31:08,519
in order to corner my king

544
00:31:08,519 --> 00:31:10,200
to the edge of the board.

545
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,039
Be careful of your bishop being besieged.

546
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:14,720
Mr. Frank.

547
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:17,079
Time to set off for the music summer camp.

548
00:31:19,039 --> 00:31:20,759
Does the breakfast not suit your taste?

549
00:31:22,039 --> 00:31:24,240
I'll talk to you later. Bye.

550
00:31:25,519 --> 00:31:26,759
Joe.

551
00:31:26,759 --> 00:31:28,440
I've been waiting for you.

552
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,119
Thank you for buying us the cake.

553
00:31:31,240 --> 00:31:33,799
I've wanted to eat this cake
for quite some time,

554
00:31:33,799 --> 00:31:35,079
but there's always a long queue every day.

555
00:31:35,079 --> 00:31:36,319
I don't have the time to buy it.

556
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,240
So you didn't buy it?

557
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:40,039
Then it must have been Eric.

558
00:31:40,039 --> 00:31:42,759
But Eric will definitely leave his name.

559
00:31:42,759 --> 00:31:44,839
Just a matchstick.

560
00:31:44,839 --> 00:31:46,720
So mysterious.

561
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:48,559
How does he know I like to eat

562
00:31:48,559 --> 00:31:49,559
this brand of cake?

563
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,799
You must have mentioned it,

564
00:31:52,799 --> 00:31:53,839
and he remembered it.

565
00:31:54,839 --> 00:31:55,960
How sweet.

566
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:58,440
He lined up to buy cake for you.

567
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,920
But I've never mentioned it.

568
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,279
Whatever, I'm fine with it.

569
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,799
Let's eat together.

570
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:06,799
Don't.

571
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:08,880
He lined up to buy it for you.

572
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:11,279
How can I finish it all?

573
00:32:11,279 --> 00:32:13,799
- Stop being so polite, go share it.
- Right.

574
00:32:13,799 --> 00:32:15,599
Looks delicious, thank you.

575
