at the Sir Robert Ho Tung Library.]</i>

576
00:33:03,960 --> 00:33:05,160
Mr. Frank.

577
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:06,279
It's about time.

578
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,680
Mr. Frank.

579
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:11,799
It's about time.

580
00:33:29,519 --> 00:33:31,200
Mike, can I not go?

581
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,039
Sorry, Mr. Wei.

582
00:33:33,039 --> 00:33:34,319
I'm not the one in charge.

583
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,440
- Alright, I hope he gets well soon.
- Thank you.

584
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,480
Okay.

585
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:58,839
You don't need to participate in today's event.

586
00:33:58,839 --> 00:34:00,240
I've already told the teacher

587
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,480
that you are still adjusting to the jet lag,

588
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,960
and feeling a bit unwell,

589
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:05,279
so you can't do any intense exercise.

590
00:34:05,839 --> 00:34:07,160
Why do you help me?

591
00:34:08,559 --> 00:34:09,639
You are my client.

592
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:12,320
Meeting your needs is my job.

593
00:34:17,079 --> 00:34:18,144
However,

594
00:34:19,079 --> 00:34:20,119
you mom

595
00:34:20,119 --> 00:34:21,719
can't know about this.

596
00:34:21,719 --> 00:34:23,760
Otherwise, both of us will be in trouble.

597
00:34:24,519 --> 00:34:25,632
Got it.

598
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:28,480
No other schedule is arranged for today.

599
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,599
Anything else that you need me to help?

600
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:34,880
If no,

601
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,119
I'll go deal with other work

602
00:34:36,119 --> 00:34:37,800
after you finish the meal.

603
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:43,000
Does your hotel have a gallery?

604
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,064
Yes.

605
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,264
Would you like to take a look?

606
00:34:48,599 --> 00:34:49,696
No problem.

607
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:51,760
I'll make an appointment
with my colleague from the gallery,

608
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,760
letting her guide you through.

609
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,616
Join us.

610
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:04,352
Casey.

611
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,559
Mr. Frank.

612
00:35:08,559 --> 00:35:10,480
This is the curator
from the Monte solo exhibition,

613
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:11,840
Josephine.

614
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,519
Hi, Mr. Frank.

615
00:35:13,519 --> 00:35:14,920
Welcome to our gallery.

616
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,159
Would you like me to introduce

617
00:35:16,159 --> 00:35:17,679
you about this series of works?

618
00:35:17,679 --> 00:35:19,360
No need, I'll look around myself.

619
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:21,360
Okay.

620
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:23,079
We have prepared afternoon tea over there.

621
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:25,280
You can try it if you're interested.

622
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:27,079
I don't eat things carelessly.
I have allergies.

623
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:29,840
Okay, then I won't disturb you.

624
00:35:39,119 --> 00:35:41,159
You've had a hard time.

625
00:35:42,079 --> 00:35:43,440
He's so cute.

626
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:48,440
I feel like such a failure.

627
00:35:49,639 --> 00:35:51,639
I can't communicate with the child at all.

628
00:35:52,199 --> 00:35:53,480
I've already done everything for him.

629
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,199
I've given him whatever he wants,

630
00:35:55,199 --> 00:35:57,280
but he still seems unsatisfied.

631
00:35:58,360 --> 00:35:59,360
I can't handle him.

632
00:36:00,119 --> 00:36:01,639
Do you want some tips?

633
00:36:03,519 --> 00:36:04,760
Any tricks?

634
00:36:05,719 --> 00:36:06,752
Go ahead.

635
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:10,000
Maybe just don't try too hard.

636
00:36:12,039 --> 00:36:13,239
But you just said,

637
00:36:13,239 --> 00:36:15,199
"Mr. Frank, we have prepared afternoon tea…"

638
00:36:23,559 --> 00:36:25,360
I was just trying to greet him.

639
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,719
But you are different.

640
00:36:26,719 --> 00:36:27,880
You're with him every day.

641
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:30,639
I don't know how long I can hold on.

642
00:36:31,599 --> 00:36:32,800
So,

643
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:34,960
you could try not to do everything he wants,

644
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,840
and then he might think you value him.

645
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,320
It seems

646
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:40,840
to be a trick what you usually use

647
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:43,000
to deal with the men around you, right?

648
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,440
He's just a child.

649
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,320
Psychologically speaking,

650
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,480
male psychology

651
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:50,400
is categorized under child psychology.

652
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:51,920
The principle remains the same.

653
00:36:53,039 --> 00:36:55,000
Really?

654
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,519
Men are like children.

655
00:36:57,519 --> 00:36:58,840
Just treat him

656
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,880
as an adult.

657
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:02,400
Don't keep thinking he's the boss's son,

658
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:03,920
making yourself timid.

659
00:37:05,199 --> 00:37:06,320
Give it a try.

660
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:07,599
It might work.

661
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,000
- Okay. Alright.
- I'm off.

662
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:24,320
Is the sea in Macau beautiful?

663
00:37:26,199 --> 00:37:27,440
Actually, the sea in Macau

664
00:37:28,559 --> 00:37:29,760
is nothing special,

665
00:37:30,599 --> 00:37:32,159
just like any other sea,

666
00:37:32,679 --> 00:37:34,599
bringing peace to everyone.

667
00:37:57,039 --> 00:37:59,039
Any other places you want to go?

668
00:37:59,039 --> 00:38:01,119
I'm tired. I want to go back.

669
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,280
Aren't you coming with me?

670
00:38:44,639 --> 00:38:45,760
Joe.

671
00:38:50,719 --> 00:38:52,800
- You're here, too? What a coincidence!
- Yes.

672
00:38:53,599 --> 00:38:54,639
What a coincidence.

673
00:38:55,639 --> 00:38:57,280
Do you also love to read here?

674
00:38:58,039 --> 00:38:59,039
I came to return books.

675
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:02,840
Returning books? I just happened
to finish this one as well.

676
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:03,904
<i>[Selected Letters of Van Gogh]</i>
I need to return it too.

677
00:39:04,639 --> 00:39:05,719
Let's do it together.

678
00:39:06,639 --> 00:39:07,680
I can carry it for you.

679
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:11,392
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

680
00:39:20,119 --> 00:39:21,519
Have you heard a saying?

681
00:39:23,239 --> 00:39:24,599
Met once, what a coincidence.

682
00:39:24,599 --> 00:39:26,280
Met twice, what a chance.

683
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:28,639
Met third, what a fate.

684
00:39:28,639 --> 00:39:29,840
No.

685
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:30,840
But I've heard a saying.

686
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,159
All coincidences are long premeditated.

687
00:39:42,320 --> 00:39:45,840
Okay, I admit, I did premeditate.

688
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:47,360
But it wasn't for long.

689
00:39:49,639 --> 00:39:50,880
How did you know?

690
00:39:52,199 --> 00:39:53,280
You just said it yourself.

691
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:57,719
Okay.

692
00:39:57,719 --> 00:39:59,639
That time at the Chinese medicine clinic,
you went there to look for me, right?

693
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:02,440
When did you realize it?

694
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:04,679
Your acting was too clumsy.

695
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,719
But there is one thing you overlooked.

696
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,480
The second time we met at the bar.

697
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:12,079
I actually went there
to look for you on purpose.

698
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,719
I remember now.

699
00:40:15,719 --> 00:40:18,239
It was when you got cozy with a beauty, right?

700
00:40:18,239 --> 00:40:19,800
- Come on, give it to me.
- I'm returning the books.

701
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:23,519
No. Here you are. Thank you.

702
00:40:23,519 --> 00:40:24,679
I really don't know her.

703
00:40:24,679 --> 00:40:26,039
I must explain it to you.

704
00:40:26,039 --> 00:40:28,159
Look at that expression of yours.

705
00:40:28,159 --> 00:40:29,760
You don't trust me.

706
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,800
- I do.
- Sorry, Miss Chen.

707
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,000
You have extra charges for these books

708
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,960
because they are overdue.

709
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:36,280
Okay, just deduct it.

710
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:38,400
I forgot to return them
because of too many business trips recently.

711
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:39,760
- Done?
- Yes.

712
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:42,440
You don't come here often, do you?

713
00:40:43,239 --> 00:40:45,000
I was away on a business trip before.

714
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:46,208
Let's go.

715
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,719
This building has been around
for over a hundred years.

716
00:40:54,599 --> 00:40:57,360
Previously, a wealthy gentleman
named Ho Tung lived here.

717
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:58,440
After he passed away,

718
00:40:58,440 --> 00:40:59,639
he donated this place to the government.

719
00:40:59,639 --> 00:41:01,239
And then it became the library today.

720
00:41:02,559 --> 00:41:04,400
You're not a local here, are you?

721
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:05,679
After all, your accent

722
00:41:05,679 --> 00:41:06,800
is a bit different from theirs.

723
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,519
My dad is from Guangzhou,

724
00:41:10,519 --> 00:41:11,616
and my mom is from Nanjing.

725
00:41:12,519 --> 00:41:13,800
Then why are you so familiar with

726
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:14,880
Macau?

727
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:16,920
After all, I've been living here

728
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:18,239
for four years now.

729
00:41:18,239 --> 00:41:19,296
Four years?

730
00:41:21,639 --> 00:41:22,719
I quite like it here.

731
00:41:23,719 --> 00:41:24,719
When I'm free, I usually

732
00:41:24,719 --> 00:41:26,599
go stroll around the old town.

733
00:41:26,599 --> 00:41:27,639
Don't you think here is more lively

734
00:41:27,639 --> 00:41:28,719
than Taipa?

735
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,776
If you're free, I can show you around.

736
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:38,239
Sure, I'm certainly free.

737
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:40,599
I'd love to have a friend

738
00:41:40,599 --> 00:41:42,360
who is very familiar with Macau

739
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:44,599
to give me an in-depth tour of Macau.

740
00:41:48,639 --> 00:41:51,559
So, are you settled in Macau now?

741
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:54,976
It's hard to say.

742
00:41:57,039 --> 00:41:58,880
I have a five-year pact with myself.

743
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:01,960
Within these five years,

744
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,119
if my career development here

745
00:42:03,119 --> 00:42:04,360
doesn't meet my expectations,

746
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:06,639
I might have other plans.

747
00:42:06,639 --> 00:42:07,648
Five years?

748
00:42:08,199 --> 00:42:10,679
Then you have one year left.

749
00:42:10,679 --> 00:42:11,920
What are your expectations?

750
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,280
- Simple.
- Shall we go over there?

751
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:18,599
To collaborate with artists I admire,

752
00:42:18,599 --> 00:42:20,400
and to create the exhibitions
I truly want to do,

753
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:23,320
without considering
too many commercial aspects,

754
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:24,360
the very pure kind.

755
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:26,496
That's really cool.

756
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,719
Most of the exhibitions I run now

757
00:42:29,719 --> 00:42:31,119
